# Testing

Run the **smallest scope that catches your regression** after substantive edits. Full gate: `mvn verify` once before marking done — see [stomp4j-quality.mdc](stomp4j-quality.mdc).

## Tiered ladder

| When | Command |
|------|---------|
| Trivial / compile-only edit | Skip until next substantive change |
| One module edited | Module command below |
| Public API or SPI | Module tests + downstream from **impact map** |
| Task done | `mvn verify` (once) |

```bash
# Fast (no Docker) — unit + embedded server
mvn -Pfast -pl commons,client,server,bridge/stomp4j-kafka-bridge test

# Integration (Docker) — drop -Pfast
mvn -pl client test
mvn -pl server test

# Single test
mvn -pl <module> test -Dtest=ClassName#methodName
```

Use `-Pfast` for unit/embedded coverage. Run **without** `-Pfast` for transport, protocol, session, broker, or `@Tag("integration")`.

## Impact map

| You changed | Run |
|-------------|-----|
| `commons` / `commons.protocol` | `mvn -pl commons test` → `mvn -Pfast -pl client,server test`; framing/commands → full client+server (Docker) |
| `client` transport/protocol | `mvn -pl client test` |
| `client` public API only | `mvn -Pfast -pl client test` (+ full if async/broker-facing) |
| `server.session` / channels | `mvn -pl server test` |
| `bridge/` | `mvn -pl bridge/stomp4j-kafka-bridge test` |
| Test infra (`broker.xml`, `*.tests.infra`) | At minimum `mvn -pl client test` |

Detail: [stomp4j-tests.mdc](stomp4j-tests.mdc) — domain language, narrative (given/when/then), meaningful assertions, Docker, cookbooks.

Test-first development (TDD) is **development guidance**, not part of this pillar — see [stomp4j-model.mdc](stomp4j-model.mdc) § TDD.

## When tests fail

1. Re-run smallest repro — [stomp4j-test-failure-diagnosis.mdc](stomp4j-test-failure-diagnosis.mdc) §1–§4.
2. Do not loop full `mvn verify` per fix.
3. After green: one report under `reports/` per §6 of that rule.

## Infra to reuse

`StompContainer`, `StompTestSupport`, `EmbeddedServerFixture` — not ad-hoc brokers or `Thread.sleep()`.
